---
import PageLayout from '@layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Guide to Sourcing Shoes from China"
  description="Complete step-by-step guide for sourcing footwear from China: finding suppliers, evaluating factories, negotiating prices, and managing production."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Sourcing', url: '/sourcing/' },
    { name: 'Guide to Sourcing from China', url: '/sourcing/guide-to-sourcing-from-china/' },
  ]}
>
  <article class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
    <h1>Complete Guide to Sourcing Shoes from China</h1>
    
    <p class="lead">
      This comprehensive guide walks you through the entire process of sourcing footwear from Chinese manufacturers, from initial research to final delivery.
    </p>

    <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><a href="#准备工作">Preparation and Research</a></li>
      <li><a href="#寻找供应商">Finding Suppliers</a></li>
      <li><a href="#评估供应商">Evaluating Suppliers</a></li>
      <li><a href="#谈判签约">Negotiation and Contracts</a></li>
      <li><a href="#样品开发">Sample Development</a></li>
      <li><a href="#生产监督">Production and Quality Control</a></li>
      <li><a href="#物流运输">Shipping and Logistics</a></li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="准备工作">1. Preparation and Research</h2>
    <p>
      Before reaching out to suppliers, you need to have a clear understanding of your product requirements. This includes:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Product Specifications:</strong> Detailed descriptions of materials, colors, sizes, and construction methods</li>
      <li><strong>Target Price Range:</strong> Your budget per pair, including all costs (FOB, shipping, duties)</li>
      <li><strong>Order Quantity:</strong> Initial order quantity and expected reorder volumes</li>
      <li><strong>Timeline:</strong> Production lead time and delivery deadline requirements</li>
      <li><strong>Certifications:</strong> Any required compliance certifications for your target market</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="寻找供应商">2. Finding Suppliers</h2>
    <p>
      China has several major footwear production hubs, each specializing in different product categories:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Guangdong (Dongguan):</strong> Sports shoes, sneakers, casual footwear - largest concentration of sports shoe factories</li>
      <li><strong>Fujian (Quanzhou):</strong> Sports shoes, outdoor footwear - home to many major brand suppliers</li>
      <li><strong>Zhejiang (Wenzhou):</strong> Leather shoes, dress shoes, fashion footwear</li>
      <li><strong>Shandong (Qingdao):</strong> Safety shoes, work footwear, OEM production</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="评估供应商">3. Evaluating Suppliers</h2>
    <p>
      Not all suppliers are created equal. When evaluating potential partners, consider:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Business License:</strong> Verify the company is legally registered</li>
      <li><strong>Production Capacity:</strong> Can they handle your order volume?</li>
      <li><strong>Experience:</strong> Have they produced similar products before?</li>
      <li><strong>Certifications:</strong> ISO, BSCI, WRAP, or brand-specific certifications</li>
      <li><strong>Sample Quality:</strong> Request samples to assess craftsmanship</li>
      <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Response time and language capabilities</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="谈判签约">4. Negotiation and Contracts</h2>
    <p>
      Key points to negotiate and include in your contract:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Price:</strong> Per-unit price, payment terms, currency</li>
      <li><strong>MOQ:</strong> Minimum order quantity requirements</li>
      <li><strong>Lead Time:</strong> Production and shipping timelines</li>
      <li><strong>Quality Standards:</strong> Detailed specifications and acceptable tolerances</li>
      <li><strong>Payment Terms:</strong> Typically 30% deposit, 70% before shipment</li>
      <li><strong>Inspection:</strong> Quality control procedures and acceptance criteria</li>
      <li><strong>Intellectual Property:</strong> Protection for your designs and branding</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="样品开发">5. Sample Development</h2>
    <p>
      Before bulk production, always develop and approve samples:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Provide detailed tech packs and reference samples</li>
      <li>Request proto samples (first attempt)</li>
      <li>Evaluate and provide detailed feedback</li>
      <li>Request revised samples until approved</li>
      <li>Approve pre-production samples</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="生产监督">6. Production and Quality Control</h2>
    <p>
      Don't leave quality to chance. Implement quality control at key stages:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>During Production (DUPRO):</strong> Check quality mid-production</li>
      <li><strong>Pre-Shipment Inspection (PSI):</strong> Final inspection before loading</li>
      <li><strong>Loading Inspection:</strong> Verify correct goods and packaging</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="物流运输">7. Shipping and Logistics</h2>
    <p>
      Common shipping methods for footwear:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Sea Freight:</strong> Most economical for large orders, 20-35 days</li>
      <li><strong>Air Freight:</strong> Faster but more expensive, 5-10 days</li>
      <li><strong>Express (DHL/FedEx):</strong> Best for samples and small orders</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Next Steps</h2>
    <p>
      Ready to start sourcing? Browse our <a href="/suppliers/">supplier directory</a> or read our <a href="/sourcing/factory-audit-guide/">factory audit guide</a> for detailed evaluation criteria.
    </p>
  </article>
</PageLayout>
